1. crear un nuevo repositorio en github
2. git init en VS code
3. git add . 
4. git commit -m "any commment"
5. git remote add origin https://github.com/ricardocarruyo/meshop.git
6. git push --set-upstream origin master

1. create a folder for the project
2. in vs code type cd + path to the project folder
3. type npx create-react-app + react project name
4. open the project folder 
5. open a terminal ctrl+shif+p 
6. type in the terminal npm start
7. go to github and create a new repository

…or create a new repository on the command line
echo "# meshop" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/ricardocarruyo/meshop.git
git push -u origin main
…or push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/ricardocarruyo/meshop.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
…or import code from another repository
You can initialize this repository with code from a Subversion, Mercurial, or TFS project.

8. go to de terminal and type npm install gh-pages --save-dev
9. add to the package.json the following

    first object 
	"homepage": "https://ricardocarruyo.github.io/meshop",
	
	scripts object
    "predeploy": "npm run build",
    "deploy": "gh-pages -d build",

10. go back to the terminal and type git init
11. then type git remote add origin https://github.com/ricardocarruyo/meshop.git

12. npm start
13. modify the App.js file 
14. git status
15. git add .
16. git commit -m "add a comment"
17. npm run deploy
18. git push -u origin master
19. go to github 
20. select the repository
21. in top right corner select settings 
22. scroll down and find the github pages section
23. Your site is published at https://ricardocarruyo.github.io/meshop/

----------------------------- For Updates -------------------------------------------------
1. create a new branch
2. git branch + name
3. type in the console git branch to see branches list
4. type git checkout + name to change the branch
5. git pull origin master branch
6. modify the project
7. git add .
8. git commit -m "comment"
9. git pull origin master
10. git push origin yourBranch
11.create a pull request 
12. select left master and right the new branch
13. you can see the changes and left a comment
14. you can add a comment for the merge pull request
15. confirm merge.

16. before any new change switch to master branch
17. delete de merged branch
18. git branch -d old branch





































